Deploy Docker App on EC2 with NGINX & HTTPS
Date: 27/10/25

Domain: example.tech (The domain you have)
Docker Container Port: 7001 → 8080 

1. Install NGINX
sudo apt update -y
sudo apt install nginx -y
sudo systemctl enable nginx
sudo systemctl start nginx
sudo systemctl status nginx

2. Run Docker Container (or through fully automated cicd)
Example:
docker run -d -p 7001:8080 --name sample-app dockerusername/sample-app:latest
Check running containers:
docker ps

3. Configure NGINX Reverse Proxy
Create a site config:

sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/example.tech

server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.tech;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:7001;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
        proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
    }
}


Enable site:
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/example.tech /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx

4. Configure Domain DNS
Type: A record
Name: sample-app
Value: <EC2_PUBLIC_IP>
TTL: default

5. Install HTTPS (Let’s Encrypt)
sudo apt install certbot python3-certbot-nginx -y
sudo certbot --nginx -d example.tech
Select redirect HTTP → HTTPS option.
Verify: https://example.tech

Note:
Security Group must allow ports 80 & 443 inbound.
